articles.author: Abid Rahman
articles.title: Michael McGrath, Tony-Winning Actor, Dies at 65 - Hollywood Reporter
articles.description: Lauded for his work in 'Nice Work If You Can Get It,' he also originated the role of Patsy, King Arthur’s long-suffering sidekick, in 'Spamalot.'
articles.content:
Michael McGrath, the veteran stage actor who received a Tony Award for his performance in the musical Nice Work If You Can Get It, has died. He was 65.
